ences in statistical behavior among the\nlongitudinal velocity derivatives, compared with the unstratified case. Since\nthe mixing process is suppressed in stable cases, small-scale anisotropy is\nalso supressed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 18 Jan 2022 12:42:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 26 Feb 2022 17:47:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-13"}
